There is a Parent Class and a Child class.
The parent class has a strong pointer to to child


1. The Child declares protocol.
2. Child declares a delegate protocol.
3. Parent confrorms or implements protocol methods.
4. Parent sets itself as delegate.
4. Child calls methods on delegate.


delegate property declaration is as follows:

@property (unsafe_undefined) id <ProtocolName> delegate;

protocol declaration:

@protocol ProtocolName <NSObject>

//no declaration defaults to required

- (void) methodNameWithParameter: (id) parameter;

@optional // optional methods

- (void) optionalMethodName;

@end